Organisers of the first Dr. D.K Olukoya Ibile Football Cup have vowed to organise a classy football development programme at the Legacy Pitch of the National Stadium Surulere Lagos between May 16 and 22, 2022. As registration of 16 non league clubs ends on Thursday (tomorrow) at the Teslim Balogun Stadium Lagos, chairperson of the Organizing Committee, Alhaja Folashade Gbajumo has declared that highly rated referees would officiate all games amid excellent medical and security arrangements. While applauding Dr. Olukoya for boosting youth football development, Gbajumo informed that the eventual champion will take home the sum of N200, 000 while first and second runners up would go home with N150, 000 and N50, 000. -Advertisement- She added that all semifinal clubs would be fully kitted towards highlighting the decency the sponsor is noted for. Gbajumo, who is also the chairman of the Lagos State Football and Other Sports Suppoters Club added that they would not compromise on discipline hence they have set aside prizes for best behaved team amongst others.